DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0378-4266(83)90059-6
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0378426683900596
AB  - There have been few studies of the effect of natural disasters upon either individual economic units or financial institutions. The present paper is concerned with the question of the evidence as to the deposit experience of financial institutions following a sizeable natural disaster. The deposit data we use consist of observations from seven individual savings and loan associations and eight commercial banks in four sizeable 1970s U.S. natural disasters. Basically, there is no evidence of a run. In most cases, there is a significant increase in deposits.
ER  - 

